sequenceDiagram
    %% Target-state flow. Current implementation exposes only metadata create and status-transition skeleton endpoints.
    actor User as Finance User
    participant Web as Web App
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant Store as Object Storage
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant Queue as Redis Queue
    participant Worker as Worker
    participant AI as OpenAI API
    participant Reviewer as Reviewer

    User->>Web: Upload invoice
    Web->>API: POST /api/v1/invoices/upload
    API->>API: Validate file and permissions
    API->>Store: Store original file
    API->>DB: Create invoice status uploaded
    API->>DB: Create audit log invoice_uploaded
    API->>Queue: Enqueue extraction job
    API-->>Web: Return invoice ID and status

    Queue->>Worker: Start extraction job
    Worker->>DB: Mark invoice processing
    Worker->>Store: Fetch invoice file
    Worker->>AI: Extract structured invoice JSON
    AI-->>Worker: Extraction result
    Worker->>DB: Save extraction and prompt metadata
    Worker->>DB: Run validation checks

    alt Validation passes
        Worker->>DB: Mark invoice validation_passed
    else Review needed
        Worker->>DB: Mark invoice review_required
    else Processing fails
        Worker->>DB: Mark invoice failed
    end

    Reviewer->>Web: Open review queue
    Web->>API: GET /invoices/{id}
    API-->>Web: Invoice, extraction, warnings
    Reviewer->>Web: Correct fields and approve/reject
    Web->>API: POST /invoices/{id}/review
    API->>DB: Save corrections and decision
    API->>DB: Create audit log review_decision
    API-->>Web: Updated invoice status
